    elif tool_call.type == "get_vendor_classification":
        if tool_call.vendor_classification:
            st.write(
                f"get_vendor_classification: {tool_call.vendor_classification.classification_code} - {tool_call.vendor_classification.classification_name}",
            )
        else:
            st.write("get_vendor_classification: None")

    # Check if this is the last message in the thread
    messages = client.beta.threads.messages.list(thread_id=st.session_state.thread_id)
    is_last_message = False
    for message in reversed(messages.data):
        if message.id == tool_call.id:
            is_last_message = True
            break

    if is_last_message:
        st.write("This is the last message in the thread.", unsafe_allow_html=True)
    else:
        st.write("This is not the last message in the thread.", unsafe_allow_html=True)
```

In this updated code:

1. We retrieve the list of messages in the thread using `client.beta.threads.messages.list`.

2. We initialize a variable `is_last_message` to `False`.

3. We iterate through the messages in reverse order using `reversed(messages.data)`. This allows us to start from the most recent message and work backwards.

4. For each message, we compare its ID (`message.id`) with the tool call ID (`tool_call.id`). If they match, we set `is_last_message` to `True` and break out of the loop.

5. After the loop, we check the value of `is_last_message`. If it is `True`, we display "This is the last message in the thread." Otherwise, we display "This is not the last message in the thread."

